    18	
    19	## 1. Purpose, gate, and the D0b reprioritization
    20	
    21	**Purpose.** Decide — cheaply, before any schema migration — whether **fielded enrichment content**
    22	(entity/alias/fact/temporal keys appended to a doc's FTS content) carries *retrieval* value at scale,
    23	separated from the length artifact. **Three-way verdict (codex Q6 — INCONCLUSIVE overrides every
    24	"FAIL⇒defer" elsewhere in this doc):**
    25	- **PASS** (`probe_15b_pass` True) ⇒ Slice 25 (D2 engine) is **eligible**.
    26	- **FAIL at power** (`probe_15b_pass` False AND 15b paired MDE ≤ `δ_d2`) ⇒ Slice 25 **defers/drops**
    27	  (record the negative; no migration on a validated-negative lever).
    28	- **INCONCLUSIVE** (15b paired MDE `> δ_d2`, i.e. underpowered to detect a migration-worthy lift) ⇒ **do
    29	  NOT drop D2**; escalate (mirror `decide_083`'s underpowered handling).
    30	
    31	**Frozen pass criterion (`probe_15b_pass`, design §5).** Enrichment *passes* iff BOTH:
    32	1. `margin_ci_lo > 0` — paired (enriched − length-matched placebo) recall margin, 95% bootstrap CI
    33	   **lower bound > 0** (content beats placebo *at power*, not just on the point); AND
    34	2. `removes_length_norm_penalty == True` — fielding/`b`-tuning removes the FTS length-norm penalty the
    35	   placebo exposes.
    36	The harness builds `enriched = {recall, margin_ci_lo, removes_length_norm_penalty}` and
    37	`placebo = {recall}` and calls `probe_15b_pass(enriched, placebo)`. **No raw-point gate** (mirrors the
    38	Slice-0 fix-1 discipline — CI lower bound only).
    39	
    40	**Eligibility framing (codex review BLOCK #6 — corrected).** A **15b pass is NECESSARY for D2 / Slice-25
    41	*eligibility*, NOT necessary for 0.8.3 parity** (Slice 20 could close the gap; D2 is conditional on 15b
    42	passing AND a *remaining* Mem0 gap — prereg `mem0-parity.md` §6). 15b decides only whether the D2-engine
    43	lever is worth building.
    44	
    45	**D0b reprioritization (un-landed; cite with provenance).** The D0b priced run (n606) — **observed in
    46	the un-landed phaseB output, `runs/0.8.3-d0b-findings-observed-by-s15a-20260622.md`; pending primary
    47	landing** — shows FathomDB trailing Mem0 by a large margin with the **accuracy gap ≫ the recall gap**,
    48	pointing at **answer-formation from raw bodies**, not only retrieval recall. (Do NOT cite a specific pp
    49	number here until D0b is landed + reported on main.) Implication: 15b sizes a *retrieval-recall* lever,
    50	so even a 15b pass may not move parity if the gap is answer-formation — the orchestrator runs the **$0
    51	gap-decomposition probe** alongside 15b to size retrieval-vs-answer-formation before over-investing.
    52	This split is recorded in the output.
    53	
    54	## 2. Method (reuse `r6_index_key_enrichment.py`, extend to the frozen probe)
    55	
    56	- **Corpus/arms:** the LME retrieval corpus + the three FTS arms r6 already builds — `fathomdb_fts`
    57	  (plain), `fathomdb_fts_enriched` (entity/fact keys appended to each doc's own FTS content — one row
    58	  per doc, NOT a graph arm), `fathomdb_fts_placebo` (length-matched, **foreign-only** vocab, excludes
    59	  the doc's own entity tokens; r6 `placebo_doc`). All LLM-free at measure time, deterministic.
    60	- **Enrichment keys (OFFLINE-BUILD, $0) — pin the endpoint, fail-closed (codex concern #5):** reuse
    61	  cached 0.8.2 extractions where applicable
    62	  (`data/corpus-data/graph-cache/0.8.2-m1-v1/extractions.json`); extract LME (and, if cheaply derivable,
    63	  the IR corpus) session keys with the **local Qwen** model. **Pin the exact local endpoint + served
    64	  model name in the output, and assert-available-or-FAIL-CLOSED** — never silently fall back to a priced
    65	  reader (that would break $0/determinism). GPU only at **<5% util after sibling coordination** (user
    66	  rule). LME-only proxy is primary; IR-corpus enrichment is a reserved follow-on.
    67	- **Key-set ↔ placebo invariant (codex concern #1):** the enriched arm uses a **frozen key set**
    68	  (r6's `entities` + `relations`/facts; if alias/temporal keys are added they are listed explicitly).
    69	  The length-matched placebo MUST be token-matched to the **full** enriched addition (whatever key types
