dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:17:    "pipeline_works_evidence": "Cheap-validate (gemini-flash-lite, 8 q across all 4 memory classes, 3 arms = 24 calls, $0.0275, 0 errors, completeness 1.0): all arms ran, per-class recall + accuracy deltas + paired 95% CI + MDE produced, atomic checkpoint + auto-resume exercised, decide_083 emitted a mechanical verdict. Priced pilot (gpt-5.4, 12 q, 3 arms = 36 calls, $0.9693, 0 errors, completeness 1.0): the priced path works end-to-end + decide_083 emitted. Resume PROVEN before spend by a backend-free kill/restart unit test (test_resume_reuses_prior_cells_and_recalls_only_absent: re-calls ONLY the 16 absent cells, zero re-spend on the 48 reused; failure!=abstention; completeness guard rejects an incomplete matrix). 12/12 d0b unit tests + 30 (-k d0b/parity/resume/decide_083/mem0) green.",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:29:      "note": "pipeline-proof on a tiny subset; NOT the citable per-class parity verdict (that is Phase B at N=606). cheapval accuracy fathomdb-mem0 deltas were 0.0 (both arms equal on the 8-q toy subset); recall deltas were non-vacuous (knowledge_update +0.5, temporal +0.5)."
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:37:    "within_20_budget_detail": "NOT <= $20 at the pilot config (~$48.95; also exceeds the aggregate $30 program budget on D0b alone). $0 cost-reduction levers (analytic, via project_full_cost): context-budget <= ~32k chars (~8k tok) -> ~$18.44 (<=20); context <= 24k chars -> ~$13.90; k=4 full-body -> ~$19.74 (<=20); k=3 -> ~$14.87. The window-fit lever is applied identically across arms (R2 invariant preserved); reducing context may lower identical-answerer accuracy (a measurement-validity tradeoff for the HITL). Phase B is BLOCKED until the orchestrator/HITL authorizes a reduced-context config or raises the budget.",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:44:      "explanation": "decide_083 was fed the cheap-validate accuracy fathomdb-mem0 deltas + eu7_recall=0.896 (the honest current eu7 point estimate per design §5) + latency_ok=true. The eu7 hard-gate (floor 0.90) fires first and correctly returns NOT_REACHED blocked_by='eu7'. This is the correct mechanical output, not the parity gap. At Phase B with the real N=150 per class, expect NOT_REACHED underpowered:<class> (manifest implied-N proxy: every class needs N>>150 for paired MDE<=eps=0.05) once eu7 clears — the per-class gap numbers still LAND (design §5) and the under-power triggers a HITL escalation (grow N vs accept), not suppression."
