dev/plans/runs/G1-reader-lookaside-output.json:3:  "decision_self": "INCONCLUSIVE",
dev/plans/runs/G1-reader-lookaside-output.json:4:  "decision_self_rationale": "AC-017 + AC-018 stayed green. Concurrent_median improved 168 ms -> 161 ms (-7 ms, ~4.2%) and speedup_median improved 3.339x -> 3.530x (+0.191x, no ratio worsening). Per handoff §6 / §8 the KEEP threshold is `concurrent_median < baseline - 1*stddev` = 168 - 11.89 = 156.11 ms; observed 161 ms misses the threshold by 4.89 ms (less than half a stddev). Movement is in the right direction but inside the noise band, so the implementer self-decision is INCONCLUSIVE. Lookaside-applied evidence captured below for the orchestrator + codex `gpt-5.4` high reviewer to confirm KEEP-or-REVERT.",
dev/plans/runs/G1-reader-lookaside-output.json:93:  "optional_sweep_notes": "Did not run the [128, 250, 500, 1000] x {512, 1200} sweep grid. Spec §2 makes it optional ('do NOT bake the sweep into the production code path'); G.0 telemetry already pointed at 1200 x 500 as the right canonical sizing for the sticky reader topology and the small-allocation footprint of the FTS5 / vec0 hot stacks. If the orchestrator + reviewer want the sweep before deciding KEEP vs INCONCLUSIVE, it can be done as a follow-up under a debug-gated env knob without re-opening the public surface; the lookaside-call helper is already isolated in `configure_reader_lookaside`.",
dev/plans/runs/G1-reader-lookaside-output.json:130:    "for_orchestrator": "Codex `gpt-5.4` high reviewer mandatory on this INCONCLUSIVE per handoff §7. If the reviewer + orchestrator KEEP, pivot to G.4 (private page cache) — that lever attacks the second-largest G.0 contention class (`page_cache` 6.29% conc with 4.01x ratio) and is canonical-SQLite (`SQLITE_OPEN_PRIVATECACHE` / `PRAGMA cache=private`), distinct from the §3 do-not-retry `cache_size` global tuning entry. If the reviewer REVERTS, the same G.4 candidate becomes the next phase since the residual is then NOT allocator-arena.",
dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2bc-S3-output.json:13:  "notes": "PR-2 reframe: kept the 0.90 recall floor (unchanged at perf_gates.rs:159) and amended ADR-0.7.0-vector-binary-quant.md to cite the CORRECTED ANN/quantization-FIDELITY measurement (recall@10 = 0.937, CI 0.913-0.957, sigma 0.0116; bge-small candle, EU-7 N=7667, K=192, standard ANN method: exclude query-source before top-10 + dedup-by-id GT). Full CI clears 0.90; R-2sigma = 0.914 -> floor NOT raised (headroom for production variance + pending N=1M PR-3). The earlier 0.828 documented as a conservative-measurement artifact (+7.8pp), citing 0.7.2-PR-2c-recall-rootcause.md. ANN-vs-IR distinction kept sharp: the floor is fidelity (GT = exact f32 top-10 over same model), explicitly NOT IR-relevance. EU-8 IR ceiling recall@10 = 0.571 recorded as a separate embedder/task ceiling (NOT a gate), citing 0.7.2-EU-8-ir-recall-results.md; lever is a better embedder/graph, not K/ANN tuning. Added fast non-gated sentinel ac_013b_floor_matches_adr asserting the constant == 0.90 tied to ADR §2 point 4. cargo build --tests clean; sentinel passes. No IR gate introduced. No §6/§7 HITL gate conflicts with keeping 0.90."
