ose (a) for Pack 1 simplicity' — simplicity flag implied (b) is structurally available; reality required it).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"sqlite-vec vec_quantize_binary requires dim % 8 == 0\",\n      \"resolution\": \"Updated 8 dim=3 test fixtures to dim=8. No production-code constraint added; production dim=768 already satisfies divisibility.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ac_007b_slow_threshold_reconfigurable timing flake\",\n      \"resolution\": \"Pre-existing on this dev-host (verified by stashing all uncommitted changes and re-running on commit 178b2b8 — still fails). The SLOW_CTE fixture's N=1_000_000 recursive CTE is dev-host-dependent. Not introduced by this slice.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"agent-security STRICT=1 netns blocker\",\n      \"resolution\": \"Pre-existing environmental limitation — 'unshare -rUn' unavailable. Not introduced by this slice.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"design_memo_deviations\": [\n    {\n      \"memo_locus\": \"D4 (Migration strategy) — 'Decision: ...DROP TABLE + recreate ... in-transaction ... vec_quantize_binary evaluated SQL-side at INSERT bind ... all inside the migration framework's BEGIN IMMEDIATE / COMMIT envelope.'\",\n      \"what_actually_landed\": \"Migration step 9 SQL is preflight-only. The DROP TABLE / recreate / repopulate steps live in fathomdb-engine::ensure_vector_partition (Rust), runtime-dim-aware, also atomic under a single IMMEDIATE transaction. The data-flow semantics (stage + drop + recreate + repopulate with SQL-side vec_quantize_binary + D3 CASE mapping) are identical to the design memo; only the host crate differs.\",\n      \"why\": \"See 'additional_changes_made_in_scope' above (dim-aware requirement).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"memo_locus\": \"D4 — 'Choose (a) for Pack 1 simplicity. Document the dim=768 hardcode in a code comment with a `// TODO(0.7.1)` if needed.'\",\n      \"what_actually_landed\": \"Option (b) (Rust-side dim-aware reshape from ensure_vector_partition). No dim=768 hardcode 