**Findings**

- **1. OK** — The design’s primary comparison is enriched vs length-matched placebo, not enriched vs plain, and it explicitly requires foreign-only, own-entity-excluded placebo matched to the full enriched addition: [dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:67). This matches the r6 mechanism in spirit: `placebo_doc` length-matches real enrichment [src/python/eval/r6_index_key_enrichment.py](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/src/python/eval/r6_index_key_enrichment.py:72), and r6’s runner excludes the doc’s own entity tokens [src/python/eval/r6_index_key_enrichment.py](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/src/python/eval/r6_index_key_enrichment.py:193). Caveat: literal r6 reuse is insufficient if 15b adds alias/temporal/fact key types, because current r6’s foreign pool is entity-token based [src/python/eval/r6_index_key_enrichment.py](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/src/python/eval/r6_index_key_enrichment.py:196); the design correctly requires extending the invariant/test to the full key set [dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:69).

- **2. CONCERN** — `removes_length_norm_penalty` is mechanical, but the neutralization rule is statistically weak. The boolean is reproducibly defined with fixed `b_hi=0.75`, `b_lo=0.00`, paired CIs, and no argmax/post-selection [dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:77). It is also compatible with `probe_15b_pass`, which only consumes a bool [src/python/eval/decision_rule_083.py](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/src/python/eval/decision_rule_083.py:254). The concern: “CI lower no longer > 0” at `b_lo` is absence of significant penalty, not proof the penalty is neutralized [dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:86). Since the explicit MDE guard is only for enriched-placebo [dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:93), an underpowered `plain-placebo@b_lo` contrast can set `removes_length_norm_penalty=True` by failing to reject. That can feed a false pass into `probe_15b_pass` [src/python/eval/decision_rule_083.py](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/src/python/eval/decision_rule_083.py:269).

- **3. OK** — The paired bootstrap lower-bound margin is the right gated quantity. The frozen function consumes `enriched["margin_ci_lo"]` as already-computed paired `enriched - placebo` CI lower bound and gates only on `> 0` [src/python/eval/decision_rule_083.py](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/src/python/eval/decision_rule_083.py:254). The design mirrors that exactly and explicitly avoids a raw point-estimate gate [dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:31).

- **4. CONCERN** — “At scale” is adequate only because the design adds an explicit 15b MDE guard; power-sized LME by name alone would not be enough. D0b’s rule already treats underpower as no valid claim [dev/design/0.8.3-mem0-parity.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-mem0-parity.md:70), and 15b correctly emits MDE and returns INCONCLUSIVE if `MDE > δ_d2` [dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:93). Remaining concern is the same as Q2: there is no separate power guard for the length-penalty neutralization contrast.

- **5. OK** — The footprint design is fail-closed against priced/airlock leakage: cached extraction first, local Qwen only, endpoint/model pinned, assert available or fail, no silent priced reader fallback [dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:60). This is consistent with the prereg footprint tag: enrichment-key extraction is OFFLINE-BUILD local Qwen, no in-library LLM [dev/design/0.8.3-mem0-parity.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-mem0-parity.md:113).

- **6. OK** — The eligibility framing is no longer overstated. The design says 15b pass is necessary for D2/Slice-25 eligibility, not necessary for 0.8.3 parity [dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:40), and it explicitly warns that D0b points toward answer formation, so retrieval lift may not close parity [dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-slice-15b-d2-proxy.md:45). The prereg also makes Slice 25 conditional on 15b passing and Slice 20 leaving a gap [dev/design/0.8.3-mem0-parity.md](/tmp/fdb-slice-15b-6b8503da/dev/design/0.8.3-mem0-parity.md:97).

**Overall: CONCERN**, not BLOCK. The design is methodologically coherent, but the `removes_length_norm_penalty` neutralization leg needs a power/equivalence guard or it can turn “not significant” into “removed.”
